Meal_name: Oats with Almond Butter and Sunflower Seeds
Food_Description: 50g oats with 1 cup nut milk, 1 tbsp almond butter, and 1 tbsp sunflower seeds.
Fresh brewed coffee with 100ml nut milk and 1 tsp coconut sugar.

Meal_name: Palak Paneer with Cilantro Lime Rice
Food_Description: Homemade palak paneer with tofu, garlic, ginger, tomato paste, lots of spinach, cashew butter, and half a block of extra firm tofu. Served with 1/2 cup uncooked basmati rice cooked into cilantro lime rice.

Meal_name: Roasted Veg Bowl with Lentils and Tahini-Dijon Sauce
Food_Description: Two small-medium potatoes roasted with olive oil, thyme, oregano, salt, and pepper. Three florets of roasted broccoli, 110g cooked green lentils, and tahini-dijon dressing (tahini, dijon mustard, lemon juice, garlic powder, water).
Notes: Filling and wholesome dinner with high fiber and solid iron intake.

Meal_name: Oats with Almond Butter and Pumpkin Seeds
Food_Description: 50g oats cooked with 1 cup nut milk, 1 heaping tbsp almond butter, 1 tbsp pumpkin seeds, and cinnamon.
Homemade brewed coffee with 100ml NotMilk Original and 1 tsp coconut sugar.

Meal_name: Palak Paneer with Cilantro Lime Rice
Food_Description: Homemade palak paneer with tofu, garlic, ginger, tomato paste, lots of spinach, cashew butter, and half a block of extra firm tofu. Served with 1/2 cup uncooked basmati rice cooked into cilantro lime rice.
Smoothie made with 1 small banana, 1.5 cups frozen mixed berries, 1 portion cookies and cream protein powder, a lot of cinnamon, and nut milk.

Meal_name: Roasted Potato with Brown Lentils and Tahini-Dijon Dressing
Food_Description: 1 medium roasted potato (olive oil, thyme, oregano, salt, pepper), 120g cooked brown lentils, tahini-dijon mustard dressing (tahini, olive oil, mustard, lemon juice, garlic powder). No broccoli included today.
Homemade coffee brewed with nut milk and 1 tsp coconut sugar

Soba noodle salad made with soba noodles, 2 tbsp peanut butter, soy sauce, rice wine vinegar, sesame oil, garlic powder, ginger powder, hot water, frozen broccoli, edamame, spinach, 1 tsp coconut sugar, and a generous amount of sesame seeds.
B_Vitamins: B1 (thiamine), B3 (niacin), B5 (pantothenic acid), B6, B9 (folate)
Notes: Didn’t feel satisfying. Not hungry but not full. Tasted bland — possibly under-seasoned. Only used soy sauce without salt, and veggies may have been too soft or minimal. Suspect protein was too low for satiety.
